channel.title: Compiling Help please
channel.description:
I've been adding some stuff onto my server, things like specials and commands. Now, when I compile it comes up with this:
[code]client.java:5991: 'class' or 'interface' expected } ^ client.java:32762: 'class' or 'interface' expected ^[/code]
Does anybody know what this means, and if so could you help me fix it. Thanks, Cazzum.

item.title: Compiling Help please
item.dc:creator: @Legend1 -Legend-
item.description:

[quote=“goneby1233, post:2, topic:125445”]try this it should work put this in your compiler

title Compiler
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_02\bin\javac” -cp . *.java
pause

it should work[/quote]

Its an error you fool, nothing to do with the compiler.
